  "prompt": "How do I filter out US election news in my Quora feed?",
  "response": "To filter out US election news on Quora:\n\n1. Click on the three-dot menu next to a post you don't want to see\n2. Select \"I don't want to see this\"\n3. Choose \"Political Content\" or \"US Election\"\n4. You can also mute specific topics related to elections\n\nIf you want more comprehensive filtering:\n- Go to Quora settings\n- Look for content preferences\n- Adjust topic and content filters\n- Block or mute specific election-related topics\n\nNote that the exact steps might vary slightly depending on your device and Quora version.",
